<header class="header">
  <h1>When to Start Seeds Indoors</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    Use your last frost date as the anchor. Count backward with purpose.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>The correct time to start seeds indoors is determined by your average last frost date.</strong>
    Count backward the number of weeks recommended for your crop. Most warm-season vegetables require 6–10 weeks indoors before transplanting, while many cool-season crops need 4–6 weeks or can be direct sown.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you know your last frost date, use the
