<section class="card">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>Should I start seeds earlier in colder climates?</summary>
    <p>
      Usually no. Earlier indoor starts do not automatically extend outdoor growing conditions.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>What if I miss my start window?</summary>
    <p>
      You can buy starts, direct sow fast crops, or choose shorter-season varieties.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can I transplant before my last frost date?</summary>
    <p>
      Only cold-tolerant crops can handle light frost. Warm-season crops cannot.
    </p>
  </details>
</section>

